"Abstract From desktops to Web sites, E-mail to call centres, customer relationship to supply chain management, businesses are beginning to invest in the next generation of IT. The explosion of E-commerce and the transformation of mobile phones to multi-functional devices will drive that trend. This article looks at how technological advances, convergence and consolidation within the marketplace are changing the shape of IT transactions. It also considers some of the legal challenges this raises for IT customers and suppliers."
